article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 64, McNeese State 57
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Anthony Paez scored 22 points, leading Stephen F. Austin to a 64-57 win over McNeese State on Saturday. Stephen F. Austin (8-6, 1-3 Southland) was down by as many as 20 points early in the game, but held McNeese scoreless over the final 5:18 of the first half to pull within 10 points by intermission. The Lumberjacks scored 47 of their points in the second half, with Paez scoring 14 after halftime. J.T. Williams scored 19 in the loss for McNeese (8-7, 3-1), and Dwight Boatner added 15.
